tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 22, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ety1665702826075.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ety1665702826075.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ety1665702826075.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ety1665702826075\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                     \n Define Application Shell Properties \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"ety1665702826075__define_application_shell_properties_32106\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">This editor is displayed to define the properties and triggers (if applicable) of an application shell.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ety1665702826075__p_d8738e1_d8739e1_d8740e1\">The type of application shell, as specified by the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Shell Type</span> property, determines the properties and triggers that you can define in this editor. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ohj1705472401504.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ohj1705472401504.html\" title=\"An application shell is a module used to initialize and run an application (Windows or character-based) or application server.\">Application Shells</a>.</p>\n<div class=\"note tip note_tip\" id=\"ety1665702826075__note_w1391ab1b7b5_w1392ab1b7_w1393ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Tip:</span> The <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Syntax\n            hint</span> provides information on the syntax or other information for the\n         selected property.</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ety1665702826075__p_d8741e1_d8742e1_d8743e1\">Use the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">More</span> tab to define your own properties.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ety1665702826075__p_d8744e1_d8745e1_d8746e1\">Properties typically have both a logical names used for display and a technical name, which may be used to address the property in ProcScript (using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$applproperties</span>) or configuration files (<span class=\"ph filepath\">usys.ini</span>). You can display this technical name by selecting <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Show technical names</span>.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ety1665702826075__topic_d6687e1_d6688e1_d6689e1_d6690e1_d6691e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d876046e95\">\n                       \n How to\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ety1665702826075__li_d4049e1_d4050e1_d4051e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dig1705473594272.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dig1705473594272.html\" title=\"Create a Windows shell for Uniface applications that run on any supported Windows platform.\">Define a Windows Application Shell</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ety1665702826075__li_d4052e1_d4053e1_d4054e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"apf1705474154305.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/apf1705474154305.html\" title=\"Create a shell for Uniface applications that run in character mode on any supported platform, such as Unix or Linux.\">Define a Character Mode Application Shell</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ety1665702826075__li_d4055e1_d4056e1_d4057e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ffc1705481850320.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ffc1705481850320.html\" title=\"Create a an application server shell when you want to define customized behavior for a Uniface server.\">Define an Application Server Shell</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ety1665702826075__topic_d6692e1_d6693e1_d6694e1_d6695e1_d6696e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d876046e134\">\n                       \n Common Properties\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ety1665702826075__li_d4058e1_d4059e1_d4060e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rex1665702714530.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rex1665702714530.html\" title=\"Determines the type of application that the startup shell executes. The type of shell determines the properties and triggers that you can define.\">Shell Type</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ety1665702826075__li_d4061e1_d4062e1_d4063e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xrw1665702585620.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xrw1665702585620.html\" title=\"Use this property to briefly describe the development object in up to 256 Unicode characters.\">Description</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ety1665702826075__li_d4064e1_d4065e1_d4066e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bck1665702654827.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bck1665702654827.html\" title=\"Extended description of the global object.\">Comments</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ety1665702826075__topic_d6697e1_d6698e1_d6699e1_d6700e1_d6701e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d876046e173\">\n                       \n Properties and Triggers\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ety1665702826075__p_d8756e1_d8757e1_d8758e1\">If there are many properties specific to a type, they are displayed in different tabs.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ety1665702826075__topic_d6702e1_d6703e1_d6704e1_d6705e1_d6706e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d876046e182\">\n                        \n Windows and Character Mode\n </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"ety1665702826075__table_d956e1_d957e1_d958e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ety1665702826075__table_d956e1_d957e1_d958e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Properties</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ety1665702826075__table_d956e1_d957e1_d958e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Triggers</p>\n</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ety1665702826075__table_d956e1_d957e1_d958e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"myt1665702689407.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/myt1665702689407.html\" title=\"Title displayed in the window title bar or browser tab when the application shell, form, or server page is run. If no title is specified, the object name is displayed.\">Title</a> (Windows only)        </p>\n<p class=\"p\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wyl1665702688770.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wyl1665702688770.html\" title=\"Specifies the library containing the global objects used by the component or application shell. If no library is specified, the library defined for the application shell is used. Otherwise, SYSTEM_LIBRARY is used as the default.\">Library</a></p>\n<p class=\"p\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"glg1665702714695.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/glg1665702714695.html\" title=\"Name of the menu bar initially displayed for the current form or application shell.\">Menu Bar</a></p>\n<p class=\"p\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nnt1665702586853.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nnt1665702586853.html\" title=\"Name of the pop-up menu object to display when the user clicks the mouse button in this component, entity, or field.\">Pop-up Menu</a></p>\n<p class=\"p\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xtq1665702714794.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xtq1665702714794.html\" title=\"This property specifies the name of the panel that is displayed with the form or application shell at runtime.\">Panel</a></p>\n<p class=\"p\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"oat1665702714863.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/oat1665702714863.html\" title=\"Specifies a panel that is available for the duration of the application session, even if a panel has been specified for the current component, or a toolbar definition exists.\">Session Panel</a></p>\n<p class=\"p\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xtq1665702714794.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xtq1665702714794.html\" title=\"This property specifies the name of the panel that is displayed with the form or application shell at runtime.\">Panel</a></p>\n<p class=\"p\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"txw1665702714934.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/txw1665702714934.html\" title=\"Position of the panel for a form or application shell when displayed at runtime.\">Panel Position</a></p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ety1665702826075__table_d956e1_d957e1_d958e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xye1665702608643.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xye1665702608643.html\" title=\"Trigger that responds to a request for a menu in a desktop application.\">trigger menu</a>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kyz1665702608722.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kyz1665702608722.html\" title=\"Activate or load the specified menu bar.\">pulldown</a></p>\n<p class=\"p\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ppz1665702665163.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ppz1665702665163.html\" title=\"Interactive trigger that defines the application-wide actions in response to the ^SWITCH_KEY action, such as loading a new keyboard translation table.\">trigger keyboardSwitch</a></p>\n<p class=\"p\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"niy1665702606431.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/niy1665702606431.html\" title=\"Trigger for responding to user-defined key sequences as defined in the Keyboard Translation Table (KTT) or defined in the usys.ini section named as userkeys.\">trigger userKey</a></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ety1665702826075__p_d8762e1_d8763e1_d8764e1\">For Windows applications, you can set addition properties to control the appearance of a background image (optional) and application window in the Image and Other tabs. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bgv1665702826148.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bgv1665702826148.html\" title=\"For Windows applications, you can define a background image, title bar, and other properties of the application window.\">Properties of Windows Application Shells</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ety1665702826075__p_d8765e1_d8766e1_d8767e1\">For character-based applications, you can define the layout of the application shell.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ety1665702826075__topic_d6707e1_d6708e1_d6709e1_d6710e1_d6711e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d876046e349\">\n                        \n Server\n </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"ety1665702826075__table_d959e1_d960e1_d961e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ety1665702826075__table_d959e1_d960e1_d961e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Properties</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ety1665702826075__table_d959e1_d960e1_d961e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Triggers</p>\n</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ety1665702826075__table_d959e1_d960e1_d961e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wyl1665702688770.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wyl1665702688770.html\" title=\"Specifies the library containing the global objects used by the component or application shell. If no library is specified, the library defined for the application shell is used. Otherwise, SYSTEM_LIBRARY is used as the default.\">Library</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ety1665702826075__table_d959e1_d960e1_d961e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jcj1665702550017.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jcj1665702550017.html\" title=\"System trigger that starts the application environment and controls the interaction of the application with the component manager.\">trigger apStart</a>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ghq1665702608876.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ghq1665702608876.html\" title=\"Reacts to asynchronous messages that come from outside the application.\">trigger receiveMessage</a></p>\n<p class=\"p\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"uwh1665702683119.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uwh1665702683119.html\" title=\"System trigger for handling any global pre-processing, such as verifying the environment or user permissions.\">trigger preRequest</a></p>\n<p class=\"p\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bar1665702683338.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bar1665702683338.html\" title=\"System trigger for handling any global post processing, such as closing a database or writing a log file.\">trigger postRequest</a></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ety1665702826075__p_d8771e1_d8772e1_d8773e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kcv1665702756074.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kcv1665702756074.html\" title=\"A server shell defines the behavior of an application server, which is responsible for executing remote components such as server pages and services.\">Application Shells for Servers</a>.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/doo1705564680445.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Executing Applications</a><p>You can execute the application using uniface.exe or make a copy of uniface.exe with your application name.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527309\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527309\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Define Application Shell Properties Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 22, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Define Application Shell Properties This editor is displayed to define the properties and triggers (if applicable) of an application shell. The type of application shell, as specified by the Shell Type property, determines the properties and triggers that you can define in this editor. For more information, see Application Shells . Tip: The Syntax hint provides information on the syntax or other information for the selected property. Use the More tab to define your own properties. Properties typically have both a logical names used for display and a technical name, which may be used to address the property in ProcScript (using $applproperties ) or configuration files ( usys.ini ). You can display this technical name by selecting Show technical names . How to Define a Windows Application Shell Define a Character Mode Application Shell Define an Application Server Shell Common Properties Shell Type Description Comments Properties and Triggers If there are many properties specific to a type, they are displayed in different tabs. Windows and Character Mode Properties Triggers Title (Windows only) Library Menu Bar Pop-up Menu Panel Session Panel Panel Panel Position trigger menu pulldown trigger keyboardSwitch trigger userKey For Windows applications, you can set addition properties to control the appearance of a background image (optional) and application window in the Image and Other tabs. For more information, see Properties of Windows Application Shells . For character-based applications, you can define the layout of the application shell. Server Properties Triggers Library trigger apStart trigger receiveMessage trigger preRequest trigger postRequest For more information, see Application Shells for Servers . Related Links Executing Applications You can execute the application using uniface.exe or make a copy of uniface.exe with your application name. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}